**Segments**

- Based on Product Type, the safety valve market can be segmented into Pilot-Operated Safety Valves, Spring-Operated Safety Valves, and others. Pilot-operated safety valves are extensively used in industries where high-pressure systems are prevalent, providing reliable overpressure protection. Spring-operated safety valves are designed to open and relieve excess pressure when the system reaches a predetermined set-point, ensuring the safety of the equipment and personnel.

- On the basis of Material, safety valves are categorized into Steel Safety Valves, Brass Safety Valves, and others. Steel safety valves are widely preferred due to their durability and resistance to corrosion, making them suitable for harsh industrial environments. Brass safety valves are commonly used in lower pressure applications where corrosion resistance and cost-effectiveness are key factors.

- From an End-Use Industry perspective, the safety valve market is divided into Oil & Gas, Chemicals, Power, Food & Beverages, and others. Safety valves play a crucial role in the oil and gas sector by safeguarding pipelines, refineries, and storage tanks from overpressure situations. In the chemical industry, safety valves ensure the protection of reactors and vessels handling hazardous chemicals, preventing potential disasters.

